#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import/Exporting"
msgstr "Uvoz/izvoz"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you attend a family party, a company meeting, a conference, or any other "
"event where other &kphotoalbum; users may be present, you may wish to share "
"your images with those people. You may of course choose to generate &HTML; "
"pages for them to browse, but given you already have spent time classifying "
"all images (Who is on the images, where were they taken etc), there are no "
"reason for them to redo all that work."
msgstr ""
"Če se udeležite družinske zabave, sestanka podjetja, konference ali katerega "
"koli drugega dogodka, kjer so morda prisotni drugi uporabniki &kphotoalbum;"
"a, boste morda želeli deliti svoje slike s temi ljudmi. Seveda se lahko "
"odločite za ustvarjanje &HTML; strani, po katerih lahko brskajo, vendar "
"glede na to, da ste že porabili čas za razvrščanje vseh slik (kdo je na "
"slikah, kje so bile posnete itd.), ni razloga, da bi vse to delo ponovili."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kphotoalbum; allows you to export a set of your images into a <literal role="
"\"extension\">.kim</literal> file, which other people may import into their "
"database, to get your classification for these images."
msgstr ""
"&kphotoalbum; vam omogoča, da izvozite nabor svojih slik v datoteko <literal "
"role=\"extension\">.kim</literal>, ki jo lahko drugi uvozijo v svojo bazo "
"podatkov, da dobite vašo klasifikacijo za te slike."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two different kind of <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files "
"exists, inlines or externals, referring to whether the images them self are "
"located in the file or at some other location. Placing the images in the "
"file has the obvious advantage that the file is self contained, while it has "
"the equally obvious disadvantage of the file being rather big."
msgstr ""
"Obstajata dve različni vrsti datotek <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</"
"literal>, notranje (inlines) ali zunanje (externals), ki se nanašata na to, "
"ali se same slike nahajajo v datoteki ali na drugem mestu. Postavitev slik v "
"datoteko ima očitno prednost, da je datoteka samostojna, medtem ko ima enako "
"očitno pomanjkljivost, da je datoteka precej velika."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two places from which you may generate a <literal role=\"extension"
"\">.kim</literal> file, namely directly from <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Export...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, or along with "
"&HTML; pages (see <xref linkend=\"chp-generating-html\"/>). Creating a "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file during &HTML; export will "
"create an external <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file."
msgstr ""
"Datoteko <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> lahko ustvarite na dveh "
"mestih, in sicer neposredno iz menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Izvoz...</guimenuitem ></menuchoice> ali skupaj z "
"&HTML; stranmi (glejte <xref linkend=\"chp-generating-html\"/>). Ustvarjanje "
"datoteke <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> med izvozom &HTML; bo "
"ustvaril zunanjo datoteko <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"External <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files will search for "
"images in one of two ways. First it will try to look for the images next to "
"the <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file, and if not found, it "
"will search for them at the URL specified when the <literal role=\"extension"
"\">.kim</literal> file was created. Notice the later is only possible for "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files created during &HTML; "
"export."
msgstr ""
"Zunanje <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> datoteke bodo iskale "
"slike na enega od dveh načinov. Najprej bo poskušal poiskati slike zraven "
"datoteke <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> in če jih ne bo našel, "
"jih bo poiskal na naslovu URL, ki je naveden, ko je <literal role=\"extension"
"\">.kim</literal> bila ustvarjena. Upoštevajte, da je poznejše možno samo za "
"datoteke <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal>, ustvarjene med izvozom "
"&HTML;."

#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno izvoza"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section will tell you about the export dialog which you get to from "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Export...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek vam bo povedal podrobnosti o pogovornem oknu izvoza, ki ga "
"odprete iz <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Izvozi...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most important part of this dialog is specifying whether the <literal "
"role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file should be internal or external (see "
"description above). You have the following three options:"
msgstr ""
"Najpomembnejši del tega pogovornega okna je določanje, ali naj bo datoteka "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> notranja ali zunanja (glejte opis "
"zgoraj). Na voljo imate naslednje tri možnosti:"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Include in <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file - this will be an "
"internal file"
msgstr ""
"Vključi v datoteko <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> - to bo "
"notranja datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Manual copy next to .kim file - Here you must copy the images yourself next "
"to the .kim file"
msgstr ""
"Ročno kopiranje zraven datoteke .kim – tukaj morate sami kopirati slike "
"poleg datoteke .kim"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Automatically copy next to .kim file - here &kphotoalbum; will copy the "
"images for you."
msgstr ""
"Samodejno kopiraj poleg datoteke .kim - tukaj vam bo kopiral slike "
"&kphotoalbum;."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Between you and me, <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files are "
"really just zip files. Normally it is not worth bothering compressing the "
"files because images normally are compressed JPEG already, and the XML file "
"itself are really tiny. If you really want to squish out the last few bytes, "
"you may still do so, by checking <guilabel>Compress Export File</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"Med vami in mano, datoteke <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> so v "
"resnici samo datoteke zip. Običajno se ni vredno truditi s stiskanjem "
"datotek, ker so slike običajno že stisnjene v JPEG, sama datoteka XML pa je "
"zelo majhna. Če res želite iztisniti zadnjih nekaj bajtov, lahko to vseeno "
"storite tako, da odkljukate <guilabel>Stisni izvozno datoteko</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The final option on the page are <guilabel>Limit maximum image dimension</"
"guilabel>. When sending some images to some friends, you may not want to "
"send images in full size, as the <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> "
"file might be huge. For this, you may specify that the maximum dimension of "
"images should be say maximum 800 pixels in each direction."
msgstr ""
"Zadnja možnost na strani je <guilabel>Omeji največjo dimenzijo slike</"
"guilabel>. Ko pošiljate nekaj slik nekaterim prijateljem, morda ne boste "
"želeli poslati slik v polni velikosti, saj je lahko datoteka <literal role="
"\"extension\">.kim</literal> ogromna. Za to lahko določite, da mora biti "
"največja dimenzija slik recimo največ 800 slikovnih pik v vsako smer."

#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno uvoza"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you select a <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file from a web "
"browser, or choose <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Import..."
"</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, &kphotoalbum; will import the database exported "
"with the functionality described in <xref linkend=\"chp-importExport\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Ko v spletnem brskalniku izberete datoteko <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</"
"literal> ali izberete meni <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Uvoz...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, bo &kphotoalbum; "
"uvozil bazo podatkov, izvoženo s funkcijo, opisano v <xref linkend=\"chp-"
"importExport\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The import wizard consist of four steps. First you must specify which images "
"you want to import. Next you must specify in which directory to put the "
"imported images."
msgstr ""
"Čarovnik za uvoz je sestavljen iz štirih korakov. Najprej morate določiti, "
"katere slike želite uvoziti. Nato morate določiti, v kateri imenik želite "
"shraniti uvožene slike."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Chances are that you call the people category <emphasis>personen</emphasis> "
"(if you are German), while I in Danish might call this category "
"<emphasis>personer</emphasis>. In the third step of the import dialog, you "
"must specify which category from the import file to import, plus which "
"categories in your database they match."
msgstr ""
"Verjetno je, da vi kategorijo ljudi imenujete <emphasis>personen</emphasis> "
"(če ste Nemec), medtem ko bi jaz v danščini to kategorijo lahko imenoval "
"<emphasis>personer</emphasis>. V tretjem koraku pogovornega okna za uvoz "
"morate določiti, katero kategorijo iz uvozne datoteke želite uvoziti in s "
"katerimi kategorijam v vaši bazi podatkov se ujemajo."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I might call myself in my databases for <emphasis>me</emphasis>, while in "
"your database I'm called Jesper K. Pedersen. Step four let you set up "
"matching for each of the imported categories. This can be see in <xref "
"linkend=\"fig-import-dialog\"/>."
msgstr ""
"V svojih zbirkah podatkov se lahko imenujem <emphasis>jaz</emphasis>, medtem "
"ko se v vaši zbirki podatkov imenujem Jesper K. Pedersen. Četrti korak vam "
"omogoča nastavitev ujemanja za vsako od uvoženih kategorij. To si lahko "
"ogledate v <xref linkend=\"fig-import-dialog\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matching People in the Import Dialog"
msgstr "Ujemanje oseb v pogovornem oknu uvoza"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the screen shot you may see that Donna is the same in both the .kim file "
"and in my database - the name is shown in black to indicate a perfect match "
"in the database. The other three names was not found in the database, though "
"both Jesper and Anne Helene was found matching as substring, so these are "
"suggested. Finally in my database I didn't have Spiff (or I might have named "
"it quite differently), so &kphotoalbum; simply suggest Spiff for the import "
"name."
msgstr ""
"Na posnetku zaslona boste morda videli, da je Donna enaka v datoteki .kim in "
"v moji zbirki podatkov – ime je prikazano v črni barvi, kar pomeni popolno "
"ujemanje v zbirki podatkov. Ostalih treh imen ni bilo mogoče najti v zbirki "
"podatkov, čeprav je bilo ugotovljeno, da se Jesper in Anne Helene ujemata "
"kot podniz, zato sta predlagani. Končno v svoji zbirki podatkov nisem imel "
"imena Spiff (ali pa bi ga poimenoval precej drugače), zato je &kphotoalbum; "
"preprosto predlagal Spiff za ime uvoza."
